  <p><strong>Common rejection reasons:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Business plan is too generic or does not match the stated sector of operation.</li>
    <li>Capital proof is incomplete or does not match the declared investment amount.</li>
    <li>Wrong entity type (sole proprietorship instead of limited company).</li>
    <li>Missing sector-specific pre-approvals (EPA, FDA, Bank of Ghana, National Communications Authority).</li>
    <li>Director or shareholder passport copies are expired or illegible.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="step-3-sector-permits">Step 3: Sector-Specific Permits and Licenses</h2>

  <p>GIPC registration alone does not authorize you to operate. Depending on your sector, you need additional permits from sector regulators. This is where timelines stretch dramatically and where most diaspora founders underestimate the effort required.</p>

