    </table>
    <p><small>All costs are indicative. Regulatory fee schedules change without notice. Confirm current fees before budgeting. Exchange rate: GHS 10.97 = $1.</small></p>
  </div>

  <p><strong>The land warning:</strong> If your business requires land (manufacturing, agriculture, real estate development, cold storage), the land acquisition and title registration process is the single most time-consuming and risk-laden step. The Lands Commission backlog is measured in months, not weeks. Title disputes are common. Diaspora founders who purchase land based on verbal agreements or through intermediaries without proper legal due diligence face a documented pattern of fraud and loss. (See: Failure Pattern FP-007, land security assumptions.)</p>

  <p><strong>The reality check:</strong> A diaspora founder registering a food processing business in Ghana should budget 4 to 8 months from first action to full operational readiness. This includes company registration (2 to 4 weeks), GIPC registration (2 to 6 weeks), FDA registration (1 to 3 months), EPA permit (1 to 2 months, can overlap with FDA), and premises setup. Founders who expect to be operational within 2 months are consistently disappointed.</p>

