  <h2 id="documents-checklist">Complete Documents Checklist</h2>

  <p>Use this checklist to prepare your documentation before engaging a lawyer. Having these ready before your first consultation saves time and legal fees.</p>

  <p><strong>For Company Registration (Registrar General):</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Three preferred company names (in order of preference)</li>
    <li>Passport copies of all directors and shareholders (certified/notarized)</li>
    <li>Proof of residential address for all directors (utility bill or bank statement, less than 3 months old)</li>
    <li>Ghana Card number (if applicable; required for Ghanaian directors)</li>
    <li>Proposed registered office address in Ghana</li>
    <li>Company regulations (articles of association; your lawyer prepares these)</li>
    <li>Statutory declaration of compliance (your lawyer prepares this)</li>
  </ul>

  <p><strong>For GIPC Registration:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Certificate of Incorporation (original or certified true copy)</li>
    <li>Company regulations (same as submitted to RGD)</li>
    <li>Tax Identification Number (TIN) certificate</li>
    <li>Business plan (sector-specific, with employment projections and capital deployment schedule)</li>
    <li>Proof of capital: bank statements showing inward remittance, OR customs documentation for imported equipment, OR certified asset valuation</li>
    <li>Passport copies of all foreign shareholders and directors</li>
    <li>Environmental permit from EPA (if applicable to your sector)</li>
    <li>Completed GIPC application form</li>
    <li>Two passport-size photographs of each director</li>
  </ul>

  <p><strong>For Bank Account Opening:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Certificate of Incorporation</li>
    <li>Company regulations</li>
    <li>Board resolution authorizing account opening and naming signatories</li>
    <li>Passport copies and proof of address for all signatories</li>
    <li>TIN certificate</li>
    <li>GIPC registration certificate (some banks require this before opening; others will open with the application in progress)</li>
    <li>Completed bank account application forms and KYC documentation</li>
  </ul>

